name: Rueben Bain Jr.
scoutingReport: Despite his size, he's still consistently beating tackles on the edge with speed. His ability to turn the corner at the arc is similar to players 30lb less than him. His strength is elite, you could line him up as a 3 tech if you wanted to. In all, a physically dominant prospect that can be moved all along the defensive line that will immediately be a huge plus in the the run game and could develop into an All Pro 10+ sack pass rusher.

name: Caleb Downs
scoutingReport: You can have him play safety, in the box, nickel, corner, he can do it all. You can even have him return punts and kicks. He won't miss tackles, he won't get beat with speed or bad decisions, he's just a great all around saftety that can do everything you could ever want a defensive back to do.

name: Arvell Reese
scoutingReport: Think Micah Parsons. He can play off ball linebacker in space, or the edge and be an elite pass rusher with his speed, bend, strength and overall movement skills. Can win with speed to power or just pure speed. A creative defensive coordinator can have him blitzing from the interior as a standup linebacker and offers insane versatility in the front 7.

name: Fernando Mendoza
scoutingReport: Accurate and good decision maker. Athletic enough that he can make a defense pay if they don't take his running ability seriously. Can throw on the run but best in the pocket with timing and rhythm. High quality human who loves football and can be counted on as a leader of a franchise.

name: Jordyn Tyson
scoutingReport: Great body control and hands, will make acrobatic catches routinely. Great seperation ability in and out of breaks and fast enough to win vertically. Can play inside or outside and wins most in the intermediate areas.

name: Peter Woods
scoutingReport: Moves very well for his size, can be a 3 tech, 5 or 1 in certain situations. Has a great ability to shed blocks in the run game almost instantly. Can be a great pass rusher.

name: Carnell Tate
scoutingReport: Boundary WR with great speed and hands. Must have someone over the top because he can win vertically.
